definitions: constituting number six in a sequence; 6th

examples.text: to the original five categories we add a sixth

definitions: each of six equal parts into which something is or may be divided

examples.text: a sixth of the total population

shortDefinitions: each of six equal parts into which something is or may be divided

definitions: the sixth finisher or position in a race or other competition
shortDefinitions: sixth finisher or position in race

definitions: the sixth grade of a school.
sixthly (used to introduce a sixth point or reason)

examples.text: sixth, given all the facts there is no logical reason why we can't make a decision

definitions: an interval spanning six consecutive notes in a diatonic major or minor scale, e.g., C to A (major sixth) or A to F (minor sixth).
shortDefinitions: interval spanning six consecutive notes in diatonic major or minor scale

definitions: the note which is higher by a sixth than the tonic of a scale or root of a chord.
shortDefinitions: note that is higher by this interval than tonic of scale or root of chord
